      "span_text": "Because overexpression of DACH1 increased SMAD4 expression and enhanced the TGF-β1 (transforming growth factor-β1) signaling pathway, it was suggested that activation of DACH1/TGF-β1 pathway switches off aldosterone production and that such an inhibitory pathway is blunted in APA (Figure 2 ). [CITATION_6] Overexpression of TGFβ1 in mice decreases aldosterone production, and decreased expression of TGFβ1 increases aldosterone Figure 2 .",
